args:
Elisanne has been distraught since reading
a secret history, and even Alex's attempts at
encouragement do nothing to assuage her
doubts. For alas, she has learned the dark
shame of the royal family: the prince died
at birth and was replaced by another!
A few days prior to the clash between the prince's\nNew Alberian Army and the Dyrenell Army led by\nLeonidas and Chelle...
A defector informs us that the imperials\nhave started their advance on the Halidom.
The decisive battle begins at last.
It's possible the force is being led by my\nbrother and sisterâ€”in which case,\nwe have a very difficult battle ahead.
Aw, those two chumps don't stand a\nprayer so long as we stick together!
Bwa ha ha! They're gonna wet their\nsmallclothes and run like hell when\nthey see ol' Ranzal comin' at 'em!
Well, I can't say I dislike the confidence.\nStill, we'd best get a start on our own\npreparations for battle regardless.
Okay, everyone. Just stick to our\nbattle plan and we'll be fine.
Is something wrong, Elly?\nYou're acting a bit strange.
N-no, Your Highness! Just a spot\nof pre-battle nerves, I imagine.
Yeah, it certainly isn't going to be easy.\nI'm sorry to keep asking so much of you.
I serve you of my own volition, Highness;\nyou need apologize for nothing.
In that case, I'm going to head off \nand leave the preparations to you.
(I cannot tear my mind from what I read\nin that history book and document...)
(Wherein lies the truth?\nWhat ought I believe?)
A-already? Damnation! We must hurry\nand get word toâ€”
I feared as muchâ€”your thoughts\nare clearly elsewhere.
A fiction I created to test you, yes.\nNow, what IS on that mind of yours?
Elly, are you still so afraid of showing\nweakness that you would seek to find the\nanswers on your own no matter the cost?
Hesitation and worry BEGET weakness.\nAnd if such weakness is made flesh,\nyou cannot hope to prevail.
Would you truly throw aside all you have\nbuilt here for such a reason?
We already lost our childhood church.\nWe don't need to lose another home.
This is not the time for mooncalf\nditheringâ€”not with the wolves\nof Dyrenell at our very door.
...You're right, of course. Pray forgive me.
Keep your head out of the clouds unless\nyou want it to end up decorating a pike.\nThe prince is counting on you.
If you're still troubled after the battle,\ncome find me. I've been known to lend a\nfine ear and shoulder from time to time.
(Alex is right. Why am I wasting time\nworrying about this?)
(Right now, I must put my all\ninto the battle before me!)

A seventh and eighth child have
been born to King Aurelius.
The seventh is named
{player_name}
and the eighth is named Zethia.
However, ten days following the birth\nof the seventh child...

He was stricken with wyrmscale.
Attempts to nurse the child to health
bore no fruit, and he entered Ilia's
arms a mere month after his birth.
King Aurelius then welcomed a new,\nadopted son into his life.
This child henceforth became the\nseventh in line to the throne,\nPrince {player_name}.
(...If that document was authentic,\nit means His Highness is actually a baby\nswitched near the time of his birth!)
(Which would mean he is not\nthe seventh scion at all...)

(No, this cannot be! King Aurelius was
famed for his fairness and forthright
natureâ€”he would never harbor a secret
of such magnitude!)

On said terms is the agreement
between our nations so sworn.

â€”Aurelius
â€”Finlorda
(The name Finlorda is unknown to me.\nAt best, it's a lesser noble who governs\na far-flung territory somewhere.)
(If the royal family WERE to adopt a child,\nsurely it would have been from a good\nfamily of suitably high peerage.)
(Which means Harle may have forged\nthe document and is using it to trick me.)
(O Ilia! Where is your voice?!\nWhy would you lead me astray?!)
(Enough of this! My questions will remain\nforever unanswered if I fall in battle now!)
